cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.PL

This paper is about continuous integration of machine learning models, which involves both software engineering practices (e.g., testing, deployment) and machine learning techniques (e.g., model design, tuning). Therefore, it could fit into several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category is the most likely fit, as the paper is primarily about developing a continuous integration system for machine learning models. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering): This sub-category is also highly relevant, as the paper discusses the importance of applying software engineering practices to machine learning development. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category is relevant because machine learning is a subfield of AI, and the paper discusses the challenges of applying AI techniques to continuous integration. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category is relevant because the paper discusses the use of machine learning models in real production systems, which often involve computer vision applications. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages): This sub-category is relevant because the paper introduces a domain specific language for specifying integration conditions, which is a programming language concept.
